  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The addition of a new storey to the original single-storey rear extension would compromise the integrity of the rear elevation to the detriment of the appearance and architectural interest of the heritage asset. The proposals would therefore conflict with Policies HE9 of Planning Policy Statement 5 (Planning for the Historic Environment), with advice set out in the Historic Environment Planning Practice Guide, with Policy 7.8 (sustaining and enhancing the significance of heritage assets) of the London Plan 2011 and with Policy CS9 (protecting and enhancing Islington’s built and historic environment) of Islington’s Core Strategy 2011, together with the expectations of Policy D28 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan 2002. The granting of planning permission would in any case be premature in the absence of any listed building consent for the proposed works."
